</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Tentorial index 0.35-0.39 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 5. Aphidius areolatus Ashmead, female A body B wing C antennae D head E propodeum F dorsal view of petiole G lateral view of petiole." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.86.70767.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/601089" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">5D</figureCitation>
). Malar space 0.27-0.30 times longitudinal eye diameter. Antenna 14-segmented, thickened at apex with short antennal segments (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 5. Aphidius areolatus Ashmead, female A body B wing C antennae D head E propodeum F dorsal view of petiole G lateral view of petiole." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.86.70767.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/601089" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">5C</figureCitation>
). F1 slightly longer than F2. F1 and F2 2.12-2.14 and 1.63-1.76 times as long as their width at the middle, respectively. Maxillary palp with four palpomeres, labial palp with three palpomeres. Ratio of eye to temple in dorsal view 1.42. Face width/height ratio 1.46-1.57 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 5. Aphidius areolatus Ashmead, female A body B wing C antennae D head E propodeum F dorsal view of petiole G lateral view of petiole." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.86.70767.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/601089" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">5D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Mesosoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Propodeum areolated, areola length/width ratio ca. 1.53 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 5. Aphidius areolatus Ashmead, female A body B wing C antennae D head E propodeum F dorsal view of petiole G lateral view of petiole." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.86.70767.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/601089" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">5E</figureCitation>
). Pterostigma 3.61 times as long as wide. Ratio of pterostigma length to R1 vein length ca. 1.14 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 5. Aphidius areolatus Ashmead, female A body B wing C antennae D head E propodeum F dorsal view of petiole G lateral view of petiole." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.86.70767.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/601089" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">5B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Metasoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Petiole 2.17 times as long as wide at spiracles (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 5. Aphidius areolatus Ashmead, female A body B wing C antennae D head E propodeum F dorsal view of petiole G lateral view of petiole." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.86.70767.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/601089" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">5F, G</figureCitation>
), with about 10 straight costulae in anterolateral area (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 5. Aphidius areolatus Ashmead, female A body B wing C antennae D head E propodeum F dorsal view of petiole G lateral view of petiole." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.86.70767.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/601089" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">5G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Colour</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Antenna black. Head black. Face with clypeus black, mouth parts light-brown. Mesoscutum and metasoma black, except for brown petiole. Legs brown with dark apices.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Male.</emphasis>
Antenna 19-20-segmented. Maxillary palp with four palpomeres, labial palp with three palpomeres.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
