<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="63" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
Morphologically, the examined specimens exhibited more variability than was known before (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-94-017-6337-0_2" author="Stary, P" journalOrPublisher="Springer Science &amp; Business Media (The Hague)" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" pagination="15 - 17" refId="B24" refString="Stary, P, Schlinger, EI, 1967. A revision of the far east Asian Aphidiidae (Hymenoptera). Springer Science &amp; Business Media (The Hague) 3: 15 - 17, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/978-94-017-6337-0_2" title="A revision of the far east Asian Aphidiidae (Hymenoptera)." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-94-017-6337-0_2" volume="3" year="1967">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Starý">Stary</normalizedToken>
and Schlinger 1967
</bibRefCitation>
). The pterostigma is more triangular and the petiole more quadrate than in the original description. 
<bibRefCitation author="Chang, YD" journalOrPublisher="Chungnam Univ" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" pagination="16 - 22" refId="B4" refString="Chang, YD, Youn, YN, 1983. On four-species of Aphididae (Hym.) from Korea. Res. Rep. Env. Sci. Tech. Chungnam Univ 1 (2): 16 - 22" title="On four-species of Aphididae (Hym.) from Korea. Res. Rep. Env. Sci. Tech." volume="1" year="1983">Chang and Youn (1983)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. areolatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="areolatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">A. areolatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from South Korea (one male specimen), but their record of this endemic Japanese species is doubtful. Due to misidentification (
<bibRefCitation author="Chang, YD" journalOrPublisher="Chungnam Univ" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" pagination="16 - 22" refId="B4" refString="Chang, YD, Youn, YN, 1983. On four-species of Aphididae (Hym.) from Korea. Res. Rep. Env. Sci. Tech. Chungnam Univ 1 (2): 16 - 22" title="On four-species of Aphididae (Hym.) from Korea. Res. Rep. Env. Sci. Tech." volume="1" year="1983">Chang and Youn 1983</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1906" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aphidius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aphidius areolatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="areolatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Aphidius areolatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be deleted from the previously known Korean parasitoid fauna (personal communication with Prof. Paik). It follows that 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. areolatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="areolatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">A. areolatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded from South Korea for the first time in the present study.
</paragraph>
